<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 07 at 2:53PM MDT until August 07 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 315 PM MDT
FOR EAST CENTRAL WELD AND WEST CENTRAL LOGAN COUNTIES...
At 251 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Willard, or 18
miles west of Sterling, moving southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters reported half dollar size hail 1
WNW of Stoneham.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Stoneham, New Raymer and Pawnee Pass.
HAIL THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
